# UnPlay Privacy Policy (English Version)

**Last Updated: 2025-12-03**

The UnPlay Team (‚Äúwe‚Äù) developed and provides the UnPlay App (‚Äúthe App‚Äù). The App is offered by UnPlay free of charge and is intended for use as is. This Privacy Policy explains how we handle information.

---

## 1. Information Collection

The App **does not collect, store, or upload** any personal data:

- No servers are used to receive or store any user data  
- No device information, usage information, or content is uploaded  
- No advertising SDKs are used  
- No third-party analytics or data-collection SDKs are included  
- No tracking or user profiling is performed  

---

## 2. Use of WeatherKit

The App uses Apple **WeatherKit** solely to display weather information:
https://weatherkit.apple.com/legal-attribution.html

- Used only for weather queries and visual display  
- Not linked to any user identity  
- Not used for advertising, analytics, or tracking  
- No WeatherKit data is stored or uploaded  

---

## 3. DLNA Casting Permissions

The App includes **DLNA casting** functionality to connect with playback devices on the local network (such as TVs, projectors, or media boxes).

- Local network permissions are used only to discover, connect to, and control DLNA receiver devices  
- No LAN or network scan information is collected, stored, or uploaded  
- No device identifiers (e.g., MAC address, IP address) are collected  
- No tracking or analytics are performed  
- No data is shared with any third parties  

---

## 4. Device Permissions

The App may request certain system permissions (e.g., location permission for weather display, local network permission for DLNA casting).

These permissions are used only for their intended functionality:

- Data accessed via permissions is not stored  
- Data is not uploaded or analyzed  
- Permissions are never used to identify users  

---

## 5. Updates to This Privacy Policy

We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time.  
If significant changes occur, we will notify you within the App.  
You may always check the latest version in the App.

---

